00:36:59.850 --> 00:37:05.658
So one of the things Google
Design Sprint Methodology

00:37:05.658 --> 00:37:09.562
forces us to do is you
have to go into the sprint

00:37:09.562 --> 00:37:12.978
with a very clear problem
you want to solve.

00:37:12.978 --> 00:37:16.430
It sounds like from
what you're saying

00:37:16.430 --> 00:37:18.830
the ExecCamp is a little
different in the sense

00:37:18.830 --> 00:37:21.710
that you walk in with
[INAUDIBLE] blank slate.

00:37:21.710 --> 00:37:24.925
You come up with either
completely brand new solutions,

00:37:24.925 --> 00:37:26.515
transformative
solutions, [INAUDIBLE]

00:37:26.515 --> 00:37:27.390
what you already had.

00:37:27.390 --> 00:37:29.362
Your [INAUDIBLE].

00:37:29.362 --> 00:37:35.278
How do you guide or
constrain the process?

00:37:35.278 --> 00:37:36.757
And do you even try to do that?

00:37:36.757 --> 00:37:39.897
Or is it just like come up
with whatever you come up

00:37:39.897 --> 00:37:43.406
with, whether it's crazy, blue
sky, 10 years down the line,

00:37:43.406 --> 00:37:46.310
or short term, it
